\cl \id 3JNlish-UK: Contemporary English Version 2000
\h1 3 John
\h2 New Testament: letters
\mt1 3 John
\mt2 John's third letter
\imt About this letter
\im In this letter the writer reminds Christian readers that they should help support those who go to other parts of the world to tell others about the Lord. The letter is written to an important church member named Gaius, who had been very helpful to Christians who travelled around and preached the good news.
\iot A quick look at this letter
\io1 1. Greetings to Gaius (1-4)
\io1 2. The importance of working together (5-12)
\io1 3. Final greetings (13-15)
